1
00:01:15,498 --> 00:01:17,834
[The summer of 2020]

2
00:01:17,834 --> 00:01:21,963
[Please wear a mask.
We can get through this together!]

3
00:01:21,963 --> 00:01:25,015
[COVID-19 PCR Testing Center Info]

4
00:01:35,351 --> 00:01:41,351
[Good Landlord Campaign! 30% rent cut!]

5
00:01:51,743 --> 00:01:56,164
[Sejeong-ro Shop Owners' Union]
[Thanks to you, I feel motivated too]

6
00:02:05,964 --> 00:02:08,051
[What a model landlord]
[Such class! You're the best!!]

7
00:02:08,051 --> 00:02:10,428
[One of a kind indeed]
Hey.

8
00:02:10,428 --> 00:02:11,932
Here's an iced coffee for you.

9
00:02:11,932 --> 00:02:14,857
I really appreciate it.

10
00:02:17,602 --> 00:02:19,891
Why is this so good?

11
00:02:19,891 --> 00:02:20,954
Right?

12
00:02:20,954 --> 00:02:24,634
Our cafe latte is ranked second in the world.

13
00:02:24,634 --> 00:02:26,115
So who's number one?

14
00:02:26,115 --> 00:02:27,593
We're really number one,

15
00:02:27,593 --> 00:02:29,872
but I dropped a spot out of modesty.

16
00:02:31,532 --> 00:02:34,359
You went and launched this cafe,

17
00:02:34,359 --> 00:02:36,115
and now times are so tough, how do you manage?

18
00:02:36,115 --> 00:02:37,934
Well, I just have to push through.

19
00:02:37,934 --> 00:02:39,651
A wonderful landlord like you, though,

20
00:02:39,651 --> 00:02:41,501
the rent break and all, it fuels me.

21
00:02:41,501 --> 00:02:43,359
Dong Gi, you give me strength too.

22
00:02:43,359 --> 00:02:46,192
With such a fantastic tenant like you,

23
00:02:46,192 --> 00:02:49,467
this cafe truly holds together

24
00:02:49,467 --> 00:02:50,843
Se Yoon Building, you know?

25
00:02:50,843 --> 00:02:52,818
It puts my mind completely at ease.

26
00:02:52,818 --> 00:02:55,818
- Right?
- From now on, everyone in this building

27
00:02:55,818 --> 00:02:58,046
gets a discount on coffee from me.

28
00:02:58,046 --> 00:02:59,519
I really can't thank you enough.

29
00:02:59,519 --> 00:03:00,942
- You know the basement storage, right?
- Yes.

30
00:03:00,942 --> 00:03:02,397
Feel free to use it.

31
00:03:02,397 --> 00:03:05,066
And if something goes wrong
while you're operating the cafe,

32
00:03:05,066 --> 00:03:06,569
don't hesitate to reach out.

33
00:03:06,569 --> 00:03:09,167
I'll have it sorted in no time.

34
00:03:09,167 --> 00:03:11,192
You're truly the best.

35
00:03:11,192 --> 00:03:12,912
Se Yoon Building, let's go!

36
00:03:12,912 --> 00:03:13,983
Let's go!

37
00:03:13,983 --> 00:03:16,835
- How about a quick picture?
- Oh, sure.

38
00:03:19,818 --> 00:03:21,392
[Se Yoon Study Center]
All right.

39
00:03:21,392 --> 00:03:23,392
Looking good.

40
00:03:23,392 --> 00:03:26,512
One, two, three.

41
00:03:27,123 --> 00:03:28,333
- Gosh.
- Great shot.

42
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:29,609
- I'll send it right over.
- Thanks.

43
00:03:29,609 --> 00:03:33,227
- Should we hang this in the cafe?
- Why not?

44
00:03:34,651 --> 00:03:37,093
Isn't the banner too small?

45
00:03:37,093 --> 00:03:38,433
Should I have gone bigger?

46
00:03:38,433 --> 00:03:39,642
That's more than enough.

47
00:03:39,642 --> 00:03:42,317
Who could possibly miss this?

48
00:03:42,317 --> 00:03:43,813
- You're probably right.
- Yeah.

49
00:03:43,813 --> 00:03:45,356
I want this place to be

50
00:03:45,356 --> 00:03:46,975
the pride of the neighborhood.

51
00:03:46,975 --> 00:03:50,035
This building is going
to be the center of it all.

52
00:04:01,372 --> 00:04:04,550
[Episode 5]

53
00:04:10,317 --> 00:04:13,058
I'm using this on Dong Gi again.

54
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:19,148
Once I set this, he'll sleep for hours.

55
00:04:22,359 --> 00:04:24,319
Your turn now.

56
00:04:26,651 --> 00:04:28,334
Okay.

57
00:04:32,904 --> 00:04:38,659
[Owner Ki Su Jong]

58
00:05:16,234 --> 00:05:17,900
It's finished.

59
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,525
Yeah.

60
00:05:25,373 --> 00:05:26,442
This is amazing.

61
00:05:26,442 --> 00:05:28,442
Enjoy your meal.

62
00:05:28,442 --> 00:05:30,692
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

63
00:05:30,692 --> 00:05:33,138
- Let me pour you a drink.
- Sure.

64
00:05:43,182 --> 00:05:45,776
[For Lease]

65
00:06:10,293 --> 00:06:12,844
Get over here and wash up.

66
00:06:24,713 --> 00:06:26,643
Dong Gi's going to be all right, right?

67
00:06:26,643 --> 00:06:28,252
The blood dried up pretty fast.

68
00:06:28,252 --> 00:06:31,446
The wound isn't too serious.
He'll pull through.

69
00:06:33,025 --> 00:06:35,053
How does everything keep falling apart?

70
00:06:35,053 --> 00:06:37,035
Where do we go from here?

71
00:06:37,734 --> 00:06:39,893
What if he's figured it all out?

72
00:06:39,893 --> 00:06:41,623
Figured out what?

73
00:06:42,325 --> 00:06:44,285
That you kidnapped someone.

74
00:06:48,317 --> 00:06:50,458
Let's take a step back and be rational.

75
00:06:50,458 --> 00:06:51,514
We can sit down with him.

76
00:06:51,514 --> 00:06:53,819
Sit down and say what?

77
00:06:53,819 --> 00:06:57,381
How about offering him money to stay silent?

78
00:06:57,381 --> 00:06:59,425
What if he pockets the cash and blabs?

79
00:06:59,425 --> 00:07:02,769
Should we have him sign an NDA or what?

80
00:07:06,766 --> 00:07:09,414
Then let me figure out

81
00:07:09,414 --> 00:07:12,863
how to approach him once he's settled down.

82
00:07:15,859 --> 00:07:19,612
I don't even recognize you.

83
00:07:19,612 --> 00:07:22,323
Were you like this when you were
sleeping with Hwal Seong, too?

84
00:07:22,323 --> 00:07:25,452
You can't even recall
the conversation we just had?

85
00:07:25,452 --> 00:07:26,828
We can handle that another time.

86
00:07:26,828 --> 00:07:29,413
This isn't the moment for it.

87
00:07:29,413 --> 00:07:31,798
How perfectly timed, that excuse.

88
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:35,221
So what exactly should I do then?

89
00:07:35,221 --> 00:07:37,054
End our marriage?

90
00:07:42,177 --> 00:07:43,942
Come on, let's move.

91
00:07:43,942 --> 00:07:46,313
Hurry up, let's get out.

92
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:03,289
[Yongdaemun District, Sejeong-ro]

93
00:08:07,243 --> 00:08:10,420
[Yongdaemun District, Sejeong-ro 52]

94
00:08:11,622 --> 00:08:13,249
[Jeon Yi Gyeong Abduction Case File]

95
00:08:13,249 --> 00:08:16,426
[Seoul Yongdaemun Police Station]

96
00:08:22,967 --> 00:08:24,468
Jeong Chang Su.

97
00:08:24,468 --> 00:08:26,092
[The Previous Owner of the Victim's Vehicle]

98
00:08:26,092 --> 00:08:28,522
Changsim Building.

99
00:08:35,313 --> 00:08:36,856
[Case No. KN_260315at]

100
00:08:36,856 --> 00:08:38,733
[Incident Report]

101
00:08:38,733 --> 00:08:40,575
[CCTV_Footage_Case No. KN_260315at]

102
00:08:50,578 --> 00:08:55,716
[Sejeong-ro Zone 4 Changsim Building Site]

103
00:08:59,337 --> 00:09:01,263
[Changsim Building]

104
00:09:04,258 --> 00:09:06,727
[Application for Viewing and Issuance
of Real Property Registry Certificate]

105
00:09:09,889 --> 00:09:12,149
[Sejeong-ro 247]

106
00:09:16,813 --> 00:09:18,439
Real Capital.

107
00:09:18,439 --> 00:09:22,669
[Owner, Real Capital & Global Partners,
Sejeong-ro 172, 28F, Yongdaemun District]

108
00:09:32,036 --> 00:09:33,329
Sign here, please.

109
00:09:33,329 --> 00:09:35,665
[Personal Effects Release Form]

110
00:09:35,665 --> 00:09:40,093
[Recipient, Jeon Yi Gyeong]

111
00:09:50,179 --> 00:09:53,190
[Effects, Car key, Cell phone]

112
00:09:55,267 --> 00:09:57,562
I owe you an apology.

113
00:09:59,067 --> 00:10:00,273
For what?

114
00:10:00,273 --> 00:10:02,613
When you interrogated Su Jong.

115
00:10:04,692 --> 00:10:06,619
You were only carrying out your duties.

116
00:10:06,619 --> 00:10:09,247
I overreacted about the whole thing.

117
00:10:11,317 --> 00:10:14,878
No, I'm the one who jumped the gun.

118
00:10:15,483 --> 00:10:17,339
Are you going

119
00:10:18,109 --> 00:10:20,342
to catch him?

120
00:10:22,482 --> 00:10:24,255
I'll give it everything, but usually,

121
00:10:24,255 --> 00:10:28,301
if we can't identify the culprit in 48 hours,

122
00:10:28,301 --> 00:10:31,144
chances are high the case stays unsolved.

123
00:10:36,983 --> 00:10:39,435
You're here early.

124
00:10:39,435 --> 00:10:41,404
So...

125
00:10:42,317 --> 00:10:44,567
How's Mr. Min doing?

126
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:46,818
- The same.
- I see.

127
00:10:46,818 --> 00:10:48,942
Offer her a beverage at least.

128
00:10:48,942 --> 00:10:51,206
No need. I'd better head out.

129
00:10:55,068 --> 00:10:57,329
I heard my mom's dining
with the commissioner today.

130
00:10:57,329 --> 00:10:59,609
I heard.

131
00:10:59,609 --> 00:11:00,958
Three billion won.

132
00:11:00,958 --> 00:11:04,462
- Excuse me?
- Mom hasn't given up on that money.

133
00:11:04,462 --> 00:11:07,764
She can't stand losing a single won.

134
00:11:18,726 --> 00:11:21,027
[Seoul Yongdaemun Police Station]

135
00:11:46,420 --> 00:11:48,638
[Personal Effects, Cell Phone]

136
00:12:25,484 --> 00:12:27,218
Hello?

137
00:12:29,776 --> 00:12:31,514
Hello?

138
00:12:47,273 --> 00:12:50,033
[Loan solicitation]

139
00:12:53,571 --> 00:12:57,325
[Quick cash OK, Loan Heaven]

140
00:12:57,325 --> 00:12:59,459
Loan Heaven?

141
00:13:07,484 --> 00:13:09,135
<i>Hello?</i>

142
00:13:09,776 --> 00:13:12,138
Is this Loan Heaven?

143
00:13:13,192 --> 00:13:16,052
<i>We don't serve regular customers.</i>

144
00:13:16,052 --> 00:13:17,554
Exclusive clientele only.

145
00:13:17,554 --> 00:13:19,658
<i>Is there some kind of condition?</i>

146
00:13:19,658 --> 00:13:21,699
<i>- I want to come in for a talk. Where is it?</i>
- Come on.

147
00:13:21,699 --> 00:13:22,851
Listen.

148
00:13:22,851 --> 00:13:25,067
We only take clients by introduction.

149
00:13:25,067 --> 00:13:26,688
<i>Try somewhere else.</i>

150
00:13:26,688 --> 00:13:28,734
Min Hwal Seong.

151
00:13:28,734 --> 00:13:31,449
I was referred by Min Hwal Seong.

152
00:13:33,567 --> 00:13:35,597
<i>Now that's a whole other story.</i>

153
00:13:35,597 --> 00:13:37,580
<i>Care to stop by?</i>

154
00:13:42,995 --> 00:13:48,383
[Authorized Personnel Only]

155
00:15:18,799 --> 00:15:22,602
[Jeong Chang Su]

156
00:15:34,815 --> 00:15:37,617
[Nam Sang Ho]

157
00:15:38,442 --> 00:15:40,133
Nam Sang Ho?

158
00:15:40,133 --> 00:15:43,248
He got caught inside
during the teardown and died.

159
00:15:44,242 --> 00:15:46,751
Probably had some drinks, I'd bet.

160
00:15:48,109 --> 00:15:49,581
Captain.

161
00:15:49,581 --> 00:15:51,349
Jeong Chang Su's building

162
00:15:51,349 --> 00:15:54,333
was signed over to Real Capital.

163
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:57,005
And that lines right up with when he died.

164
00:15:57,005 --> 00:15:58,464
If you could just get me a search warrant...

165
00:15:58,464 --> 00:16:00,222
Hey.

166
00:16:00,222 --> 00:16:02,620
This is another gut feeling thing, isn't it?

167
00:16:02,620 --> 00:16:04,769
Does this have to do with Gyun?

168
00:16:07,657 --> 00:16:10,818
I'm drowning in work, stop making a fuss.

169
00:16:10,818 --> 00:16:12,603
Hey,

170
00:16:12,603 --> 00:16:16,614
just write this up as a routine accident.

171
00:16:17,983 --> 00:16:19,443
What?

172
00:16:19,443 --> 00:16:22,052
You told me to find proof of Chang Su's death,
so here it is.

173
00:16:22,052 --> 00:16:24,951
Why won't you let me investigate?

174
00:16:24,951 --> 00:16:27,776
Wait, is this still because I reported you

175
00:16:27,776 --> 00:16:29,272
to Internal Affairs back then?

176
00:16:29,272 --> 00:16:31,038
You little punk, that...

177
00:16:31,038 --> 00:16:32,245
That was a lifetime ago.

178
00:16:32,245 --> 00:16:33,275
Then what's your reason?

179
00:16:33,275 --> 00:16:35,091
Darn it.

180
00:16:41,633 --> 00:16:43,799
Ju Ran.

181
00:16:43,799 --> 00:16:46,739
Let's just play by the rules, okay?

182
00:16:46,739 --> 00:16:49,606
You need results to get promoted too.

183
00:16:53,275 --> 00:16:54,680
Never mind.

184
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,651
Skip all that.

185
00:16:56,651 --> 00:16:59,640
Do you know an advisor named Nam Sang Ho?

186
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:00,901
I heard he's a city official.

187
00:17:00,901 --> 00:17:02,577
[Nam Sang Ho]

188
00:17:05,657 --> 00:17:07,415
No, I don't.

189
00:17:09,067 --> 00:17:11,371
Who is this guy?

190
00:17:11,371 --> 00:17:13,983
It was found on Chang Su's body.

191
00:17:13,983 --> 00:17:16,507
Hey, come here.

192
00:17:17,776 --> 00:17:19,044
Hey,

193
00:17:19,044 --> 00:17:21,588
I've got a whole stack of politician cards too.

194
00:17:21,588 --> 00:17:22,923
Look.

195
00:17:22,923 --> 00:17:26,316
Central Policy Institute, inspector.

196
00:17:26,316 --> 00:17:27,900
I'm only bringing this up out of concern.

197
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:29,889
Stay away from politicians.

198
00:17:29,889 --> 00:17:32,899
Pick the wrong one and you're dead meat.

199
00:18:04,317 --> 00:18:05,983
Have your meal.

200
00:18:05,983 --> 00:18:07,600
Yeah.

201
00:18:08,552 --> 00:18:11,014
[Dad, is something wrong?]

202
00:18:11,014 --> 00:18:12,939
No, it's nothing.

203
00:18:27,487 --> 00:18:30,331
[The egg custard tastes great]

204
00:18:30,991 --> 00:18:33,293
I got the seasoning just right today.

205
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:36,790
Honey.

206
00:18:36,790 --> 00:18:38,965
I don't have an appetite.

207
00:18:41,458 --> 00:18:44,922
I'm going to work ahead of you.

208
00:18:44,922 --> 00:18:47,238
[Dad, why aren't you eating first?]

209
00:18:47,238 --> 00:18:49,676
There's someone at the building

210
00:18:49,676 --> 00:18:53,765
who's desperately waiting for me.

211
00:18:53,765 --> 00:18:55,421
Sorry.

212
00:19:02,940 --> 00:19:05,575
[What's wrong with him?]

213
00:19:06,279 --> 00:19:08,369
Don't worry about it.

214
00:19:09,905 --> 00:19:13,583
His blood type is O, right?

215
00:19:15,327 --> 00:19:19,331
[Right, he's O, you're B, and I'm B]

216
00:19:19,331 --> 00:19:22,300
[How come you're asking out of the blue?]

217
00:19:35,813 --> 00:19:37,734
One iced Americano, ready.

218
00:19:37,734 --> 00:19:39,334
Why is it taking so long today?

219
00:19:39,334 --> 00:19:40,984
I'm sorry. Welcome.

220
00:19:40,984 --> 00:19:44,155
- Two iced Americanos, please.
- Two, got it.

221
00:19:46,609 --> 00:19:48,533
Can I place my order?

222
00:19:48,533 --> 00:19:50,213
Hold on, please.

223
00:19:50,213 --> 00:19:52,114
I'm really pressed for time here.

224
00:19:52,114 --> 00:19:53,574
One chocolate latte for me, please.

225
00:19:53,574 --> 00:19:55,708
Yes, sorry, one moment please.

226
00:19:57,995 --> 00:20:02,040
Where the hell is the boss?
Did he get wasted again?

227
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:04,342
[Boss]

228
00:20:13,885 --> 00:20:16,062
[Part-timer 7]

229
00:20:20,393 --> 00:20:22,384
Tough day, huh.

230
00:20:22,384 --> 00:20:25,899
What the hell is all this?

231
00:20:25,899 --> 00:20:27,818
A landlord puts a knife in his tenant

232
00:20:27,818 --> 00:20:29,827
and locks him away? Is this for real?

233
00:20:29,827 --> 00:20:31,107
Dong Gi, I am so sorry.

234
00:20:31,107 --> 00:20:32,696
It was unintentional, I promise.

235
00:20:32,696 --> 00:20:35,574
I'm serious.

236
00:20:35,574 --> 00:20:39,245
I'm shivering and my head's spinning.
I really have to get to a hospital.

237
00:20:39,245 --> 00:20:42,916
Okay. Are you hungry? I brought some food.

238
00:20:42,916 --> 00:20:45,716
Do you know I wet myself all night?

239
00:20:48,499 --> 00:20:50,930
It's fine, it all dried.

240
00:20:52,109 --> 00:20:54,849
Just release me right now,

241
00:20:54,849 --> 00:20:57,305
and I'll forget any of this ever happened.

242
00:20:57,305 --> 00:20:59,561
Dong Gi, here...

243
00:20:59,561 --> 00:21:01,942
Have a sandwich, okay?

244
00:21:01,942 --> 00:21:03,018
Bread's

245
00:21:03,018 --> 00:21:04,936
not easy to eat on your back,

246
00:21:04,936 --> 00:21:07,400
so just the egg and ham filling,

247
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:09,449
have a go at that for now.

248
00:21:10,067 --> 00:21:11,659
Here.

249
00:21:12,526 --> 00:21:14,942
Easy there.

250
00:21:14,942 --> 00:21:18,666
And it wasn't a knife, it was scissors.

251
00:21:20,609 --> 00:21:21,734
Have some water.

252
00:21:21,734 --> 00:21:24,289
Drink some water.

253
00:21:24,289 --> 00:21:27,008
Slowly.

254
00:21:31,690 --> 00:21:33,776
This is

255
00:21:33,776 --> 00:21:35,844
our cafe's sandwich, right?

256
00:21:35,844 --> 00:21:37,810
Yes, that's right.

257
00:21:38,942 --> 00:21:40,836
Is the cafe managing all right?

258
00:21:40,836 --> 00:21:44,442
The part-timer's handling it as we speak.

259
00:21:48,688 --> 00:21:51,536
So what do you intend to do with me?

260
00:21:51,536 --> 00:21:53,442
You wouldn't actually kill me, would you?

261
00:21:53,442 --> 00:21:54,863
Come on.

262
00:21:54,863 --> 00:21:57,532
Don't even say something that terrible.

263
00:21:57,532 --> 00:21:59,903
Then let's wrap this up right here.

264
00:21:59,903 --> 00:22:01,812
Please just get me to a hospital.

265
00:22:01,812 --> 00:22:04,576
Fine, just be patient a little, okay?

266
00:22:06,011 --> 00:22:07,208
- Seriously?
- Yes.

267
00:22:07,208 --> 00:22:09,342
- You're letting me go?
- Yes.

268
00:22:10,859 --> 00:22:13,214
Then I give you my word

269
00:22:13,214 --> 00:22:14,891
I won't say

270
00:22:14,891 --> 00:22:19,894
anything about your wife
and your friend's affair.

271
00:22:20,942 --> 00:22:23,230
How did you find that out?

272
00:22:23,230 --> 00:22:26,609
You two were talking right in front of me
yesterday while I was tied up.

273
00:22:27,630 --> 00:22:30,112
Wait, I'm still eating this...

274
00:23:06,266 --> 00:23:08,776
[Loan Heaven]

275
00:23:08,776 --> 00:23:10,444
Hey.

276
00:23:11,271 --> 00:23:13,231
We've met before, haven't we?

277
00:23:13,231 --> 00:23:15,523
I'm not sure we have.

278
00:23:15,523 --> 00:23:17,570
You're Mr. Min's wife.

279
00:23:17,570 --> 00:23:21,694
- Yes.
- Is he still in the hospital?

280
00:23:22,442 --> 00:23:24,122
That's right.

281
00:23:24,122 --> 00:23:27,237
He's really got to pull himself together
and get up and moving.

282
00:23:27,237 --> 00:23:31,416
So he can settle his debt with me.

283
00:23:31,416 --> 00:23:33,293
Your husband

284
00:23:33,293 --> 00:23:36,057
has no credibility whatsoever.

285
00:23:36,057 --> 00:23:37,674
Credibility is everything.

286
00:23:37,674 --> 00:23:39,770
Don't you agree?

287
00:23:39,770 --> 00:23:41,559
How much does he owe?

288
00:23:46,150 --> 00:23:48,810
With interest and everything,

289
00:23:48,810 --> 00:23:50,735
it comes to 800 million won.

290
00:23:54,859 --> 00:23:56,465
Did he only borrow money?

291
00:23:56,465 --> 00:23:57,706
What do you mean by that?

292
00:23:57,706 --> 00:24:00,845
Did you lend him a car or sell him one?

293
00:24:00,845 --> 00:24:02,657
We're a lending business.

294
00:24:02,657 --> 00:24:04,241
We don't deal in used cars.

295
00:24:04,241 --> 00:24:06,109
What about ghost cars?

296
00:24:06,109 --> 00:24:08,275
Ghost cars?

297
00:24:08,275 --> 00:24:10,905
What should I do with this lady?

298
00:24:10,905 --> 00:24:13,825
Hey, unregistered cars break the law.

299
00:24:13,825 --> 00:24:16,052
Money lending is lawful.

300
00:24:17,442 --> 00:24:21,109
Are you in a position to pay?

301
00:24:21,109 --> 00:24:23,470
I was about to start seizure proceedings

302
00:24:23,470 --> 00:24:25,895
since we haven't heard from anyone.

303
00:24:27,676 --> 00:24:29,392
- Account number.
- Excuse me?

304
00:24:29,392 --> 00:24:31,142
Account number.

305
00:24:31,142 --> 00:24:33,277
You do want the money, right?

306
00:24:34,771 --> 00:24:39,097
9402811957238.

307
00:24:39,097 --> 00:24:41,494
Nara Bank.

308
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:44,705
Check your account.

309
00:24:48,118 --> 00:24:51,234
[Nara Bank, Deposit 800,000,000 won]

310
00:24:51,234 --> 00:24:54,256
You don't mess around.

311
00:24:55,375 --> 00:24:57,253
Hey.

312
00:24:57,253 --> 00:25:00,916
Should you need anything, give me a ring.

313
00:25:07,470 --> 00:25:08,776
[Yeonhwajin Medical Clinic]

314
00:25:08,776 --> 00:25:10,050
Hi.

315
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:11,774
Ae Su.

316
00:25:20,667 --> 00:25:22,112
What?

317
00:25:22,112 --> 00:25:23,279
Want a smoke?

318
00:25:23,279 --> 00:25:25,196
Like old times?

319
00:25:25,196 --> 00:25:27,164
No.

320
00:25:27,904 --> 00:25:30,995
You used to trash me for dealing,

321
00:25:30,995 --> 00:25:33,003
and now you come around?

322
00:25:34,109 --> 00:25:36,132
There's a reason I'm here.

323
00:25:37,667 --> 00:25:40,672
But this stuff is clean, right?

324
00:25:40,672 --> 00:25:42,284
Yeah.

325
00:25:42,284 --> 00:25:46,559
That doctor is practically dying,
he's not checking on a single thing.

326
00:25:47,906 --> 00:25:50,771
You doing okay?

327
00:25:52,432 --> 00:25:54,811
Living the dream.

328
00:25:56,567 --> 00:25:58,571
Just don't get caught.

329
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:02,700
Don't worry.

330
00:26:04,821 --> 00:26:06,983
But about the money...

331
00:26:06,983 --> 00:26:09,915
Forget it. What's money between us?

332
00:26:11,453 --> 00:26:13,338
Thanks.

333
00:26:14,205 --> 00:26:16,021
Have a smoke.

334
00:26:21,711 --> 00:26:24,967
I can't believe I'm donating blood.

335
00:26:24,967 --> 00:26:27,057
My head's spinning.

336
00:26:31,805 --> 00:26:33,765
What is that thing?

337
00:26:33,765 --> 00:26:35,101
It's to put on him.

338
00:26:35,101 --> 00:26:38,818
If we want to have a conversation,
he's got to feel at ease.

339
00:26:38,818 --> 00:26:40,352
He has to be able to feed himself

340
00:26:40,352 --> 00:26:43,610
and go to the bathroom alone.

341
00:26:43,610 --> 00:26:47,195
You hold onto the key for the handcuffs.

342
00:26:47,195 --> 00:26:49,364
Where did those handcuffs come from?

343
00:26:49,364 --> 00:26:50,731
Where do you suppose?

344
00:26:50,731 --> 00:26:52,577
I picked them up at a shop that sells them.

345
00:26:52,577 --> 00:26:54,871
A sex shop? Seriously?

346
00:26:54,871 --> 00:26:57,690
You put those on with Hwal Seong, didn't you?

347
00:26:57,690 --> 00:26:59,624
That twisted freak Hwal Seong

348
00:26:59,624 --> 00:27:01,876
must've had you wear them for his thrills...

349
00:27:01,876 --> 00:27:03,234
Damn it.

350
00:27:03,234 --> 00:27:04,508
Are you out of your mind?

351
00:27:04,508 --> 00:27:05,769
Is that honestly what matters right now?

352
00:27:05,769 --> 00:27:07,217
You're the one who's crazy here.

353
00:27:07,217 --> 00:27:09,892
How could you sleep with my own friend?

354
00:27:10,705 --> 00:27:12,906
I'm truly sorry.

355
00:27:12,906 --> 00:27:14,514
If you can't forgive me, let's divorce.

356
00:27:14,514 --> 00:27:15,965
But

357
00:27:15,965 --> 00:27:18,645
let's deal with what's in front of us first,
then we'll talk.

358
00:27:18,645 --> 00:27:21,001
I want to work through us first.

359
00:27:21,001 --> 00:27:23,808
My feelings aren't even on your radar?

360
00:27:23,808 --> 00:27:27,284
That video is still stuck in my head.

361
00:27:28,206 --> 00:27:29,394
I'm sorry.

362
00:27:29,394 --> 00:27:31,442
It won't ever happen again.

363
00:27:31,442 --> 00:27:34,234
Seon, when a woman has an affair,

364
00:27:34,234 --> 00:27:36,484
it's not like when a man does.

365
00:27:36,484 --> 00:27:39,380
It's because she actually loves him.

366
00:27:41,888 --> 00:27:44,520
No, it wasn't anything like that.

367
00:27:44,520 --> 00:27:48,146
I slipped up and so did you.

368
00:27:48,146 --> 00:27:51,192
The point is now we both know.

369
00:27:51,192 --> 00:27:53,853
But I never stepped out on you.

370
00:28:00,150 --> 00:28:01,354
All done.

371
00:28:01,354 --> 00:28:04,652
How did things go when you spoke earlier?

372
00:28:04,652 --> 00:28:07,449
He offered to drop it all if we released him.

373
00:28:08,211 --> 00:28:10,160
Did he sound believable?

374
00:28:11,017 --> 00:28:12,438
How am I supposed to believe him?

375
00:28:12,438 --> 00:28:14,540
I can't even rely on my own wife.

376
00:28:16,127 --> 00:28:17,871
Let's try talking him into it. If that fails...

377
00:28:17,871 --> 00:28:19,873
Then what?

378
00:28:19,873 --> 00:28:21,291
Then we have to make a choice.

379
00:28:21,291 --> 00:28:23,757
Our family, or this man.

380
00:28:43,317 --> 00:28:45,379
Hey.

381
00:28:45,379 --> 00:28:47,573
There's nothing else, right?

382
00:29:02,539 --> 00:29:05,166
[Mrs. Jeong]

383
00:29:05,166 --> 00:29:06,859
[Are you hitting on me?]

384
00:29:06,859 --> 00:29:10,159
[I'm not. I'm telling the truth.
I genuinely enjoy your presence the most]

385
00:29:13,589 --> 00:29:16,094
[Yeonhwajin Medical Clinic Nurse Ju]

386
00:29:16,094 --> 00:29:20,316
[Did you make the payment?]
[Payment done]

387
00:29:49,983 --> 00:29:52,651
What's this about?

388
00:29:52,651 --> 00:29:54,765
He had an affair?

389
00:30:01,165 --> 00:30:02,891
No.

390
00:30:04,058 --> 00:30:06,210
[Send Message]

391
00:30:08,730 --> 00:30:11,681
[She's so hollow inside.
But you? You're the real deal]

392
00:30:14,611 --> 00:30:16,211
[I'm an older, married woman with a kid.
Why do you even want to be with me?]

393
00:30:16,211 --> 00:30:18,228
[Let's meet up. I'll cheer you up]

394
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:21,001
[She's totally vain and hasn't grown up at all]

395
00:30:38,636 --> 00:30:40,697
Hello?

396
00:30:40,697 --> 00:30:43,272
Yeah, where are you?

397
00:30:44,067 --> 00:30:45,226
<i>I'm at the hospital.</i>

398
00:30:45,226 --> 00:30:46,257
Why?

399
00:30:46,257 --> 00:30:48,037
Is something wrong?

400
00:30:48,037 --> 00:30:50,988
<i>No, I'm just a little tired.</i>

401
00:30:52,066 --> 00:30:54,694
When are you setting up that meeting?

402
00:30:54,694 --> 00:30:57,303
The Se Yoon Building owner, I mean.

403
00:30:57,303 --> 00:30:59,317
Just be patient for a bit.

404
00:30:59,317 --> 00:31:01,242
<i>Why are you taking so long?</i>

405
00:31:01,242 --> 00:31:03,417
<i>Hurry up and get it done.</i>

406
00:31:03,417 --> 00:31:04,578
I said I got it,

407
00:31:04,578 --> 00:31:07,171
so please stop pushing.

408
00:31:24,931 --> 00:31:27,350
[How to kill a person]

409
00:31:27,350 --> 00:31:29,359
[How the Mafia Kills People]

410
00:31:36,651 --> 00:31:40,037
[How to kill without pain]

411
00:31:43,616 --> 00:31:47,294
[A natural, painless death]

412
00:32:05,515 --> 00:32:06,681
<i>Then we have to make a choice.</i>

413
00:32:06,681 --> 00:32:09,525
<i>Our family, or this man.</i>

414
00:32:32,983 --> 00:32:35,092
No.

415
00:32:49,893 --> 00:32:52,234
This is pretty heavy, actually.

416
00:33:07,742 --> 00:33:10,210
[What are you doing?]

417
00:33:13,525 --> 00:33:17,551
Something malfunctioned at the building.

418
00:33:18,419 --> 00:33:21,042
[Seems like you're the one malfunctioning]

419
00:33:21,042 --> 00:33:23,299
Come on...

420
00:33:23,299 --> 00:33:26,096
I'm perfectly fine and healthy.

421
00:33:27,887 --> 00:33:30,105
Wait.

422
00:33:33,359 --> 00:33:35,144
It's nothing.

423
00:33:35,144 --> 00:33:40,699
[Ugh... You've been off lately,
pull it together!]

424
00:33:42,237 --> 00:33:44,737
Oh wait, this just came to me.

425
00:33:44,737 --> 00:33:47,700
I love you.

426
00:33:52,747 --> 00:33:55,143
Oh, thank you.

427
00:34:07,400 --> 00:34:08,818
Hey.

428
00:34:08,818 --> 00:34:10,562
You brought it?

429
00:34:18,442 --> 00:34:20,192
Open it up.

430
00:34:20,192 --> 00:34:22,032
Here it is.

431
00:34:23,422 --> 00:34:24,783
Ugly.

432
00:34:24,783 --> 00:34:27,081
Close it, quickly.

433
00:34:27,081 --> 00:34:29,561
I believed he was my man,

434
00:34:29,561 --> 00:34:32,626
but he was doing dirty work behind my back.

435
00:34:33,481 --> 00:34:34,787
Anyway,

436
00:34:34,787 --> 00:34:37,456
good work taking care of it.

437
00:34:37,456 --> 00:34:39,586
It was no trouble at all.

438
00:34:40,543 --> 00:34:42,386
You're

439
00:34:43,150 --> 00:34:45,182
quick on your feet.

440
00:34:45,182 --> 00:34:46,692
I like that energy.

441
00:34:46,692 --> 00:34:48,303
So,

442
00:34:48,303 --> 00:34:51,603
what happened
with that Senior Managing Director?

443
00:34:52,430 --> 00:34:55,766
He returned to the States.

444
00:34:55,766 --> 00:34:58,104
Without even saying goodbye?

445
00:34:58,104 --> 00:35:01,363
He's got no manners.

446
00:35:03,900 --> 00:35:05,945
Just as well.

447
00:35:05,945 --> 00:35:08,821
Useless at his work but loved to posture.

448
00:35:08,821 --> 00:35:10,747
I never cared for the guy.

449
00:35:12,283 --> 00:35:14,233
What was your name again?

450
00:35:14,233 --> 00:35:16,153
Yo Na, sir.

451
00:35:16,153 --> 00:35:18,088
Are you Korean Japanese or something?

452
00:35:19,692 --> 00:35:21,591
Something like that.

453
00:35:22,568 --> 00:35:24,567
Something like that?

454
00:35:24,567 --> 00:35:26,047
So...

455
00:35:26,047 --> 00:35:29,010
Some sort of fixer, then?

456
00:35:29,010 --> 00:35:30,983
Whatever you are,

457
00:35:30,983 --> 00:35:32,248
do well from here on.

458
00:35:32,248 --> 00:35:36,534
I don't care about age, gender, none of that.

459
00:35:36,534 --> 00:35:39,018
Only ability matters.

460
00:35:39,018 --> 00:35:40,114
Got it?

461
00:35:40,114 --> 00:35:42,195
Just leave it to me.

462
00:35:43,898 --> 00:35:45,983
Bold and fearless.

463
00:35:45,983 --> 00:35:47,317
That's the spirit of youth.

464
00:35:47,317 --> 00:35:48,903
Way better

465
00:35:48,903 --> 00:35:52,403
than that sneaky bastard Morgan.

466
00:35:52,403 --> 00:35:54,609
Anyway,

467
00:35:54,609 --> 00:35:57,336
clean up after this properly.

468
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:12,604
We don't know where Morgan Lee is.

469
00:36:13,388 --> 00:36:16,773
We're still looking. And...

470
00:36:19,642 --> 00:36:22,395
The Sejeong-ro project.

471
00:36:22,395 --> 00:36:25,648
I'm handling the case.

472
00:36:25,648 --> 00:36:29,277
I've already contacted the key city official.

473
00:36:31,279 --> 00:36:35,136
Looks like we'll have good news soon.

474
00:36:40,275 --> 00:36:43,418
Are you going to keep working with that guy?

475
00:36:43,418 --> 00:36:45,442
Nouveau City.

476
00:36:45,442 --> 00:36:48,470
Just until we're done with that.

477
00:36:51,275 --> 00:36:53,043
What about him?

478
00:36:55,482 --> 00:36:58,183
Put him in there.

479
00:36:58,183 --> 00:37:00,232
So it doesn't show.

480
00:37:21,581 --> 00:37:23,880
You're incredibly thorough.

481
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:27,884
Your wife must be well-versed in this.

482
00:37:29,211 --> 00:37:31,840
When are you going to release me?

483
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:34,942
If the people around me find out,
they'll think something's off.

484
00:37:34,942 --> 00:37:38,480
That's exactly what I want to discuss
with you today.

485
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:40,412
I need your word

486
00:37:40,412 --> 00:37:44,151
that after you walk out,
you'll keep completely silent.

487
00:37:45,436 --> 00:37:47,060
Yes.

488
00:37:47,060 --> 00:37:49,960
Trust me, I want the same thing.

489
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:51,601
You spotted the cash, didn't you?

490
00:37:51,601 --> 00:37:52,859
I did.

491
00:37:52,859 --> 00:37:54,275
You were looking to grab it, right?

492
00:37:54,275 --> 00:37:56,241
Level with me here.

493
00:37:56,241 --> 00:37:58,859
Yeah, so I shoved it in the bag.

494
00:37:58,859 --> 00:38:00,818
Do you even know what that money's for?

495
00:38:00,818 --> 00:38:03,583
I need total honesty from you today.

496
00:38:03,583 --> 00:38:05,589
It was a kidnapping, right?

497
00:38:06,362 --> 00:38:09,317
Ah, so that's how you see it.

498
00:38:09,317 --> 00:38:11,567
Back when I was

499
00:38:11,567 --> 00:38:14,043
helping you haul that suitcase...

500
00:38:14,043 --> 00:38:17,526
Hoisting it up like this...

501
00:38:17,526 --> 00:38:19,692
Like this...

502
00:38:19,692 --> 00:38:21,605
There was someone inside, right?

503
00:38:25,103 --> 00:38:27,647
Look, I've been honest with you.

504
00:38:27,647 --> 00:38:29,859
I'll keep the secret, I swear.

505
00:38:29,859 --> 00:38:32,024
Why on earth would I go spreading this?

506
00:38:32,024 --> 00:38:33,734
What's in it for me?

507
00:38:33,734 --> 00:38:36,342
If anything, keeping silent
actually benefits me.

508
00:38:36,342 --> 00:38:37,958
Don't you think?

509
00:38:39,008 --> 00:38:41,500
Hand over the money and I stay quiet.

510
00:38:43,371 --> 00:38:45,339
Look...

511
00:38:46,583 --> 00:38:48,772
What's your price?

512
00:38:50,810 --> 00:38:53,237
How about roughly a billion won?

513
00:38:53,237 --> 00:38:55,358
Don't just pull a figure out of thin air.
Be realistic.

514
00:38:55,358 --> 00:38:57,051
Where would we get that kind of money?

515
00:38:57,051 --> 00:38:59,234
Why wouldn't you have it?

516
00:38:59,234 --> 00:39:01,757
I can tell that much just by looking.

517
00:39:01,757 --> 00:39:04,977
Okay. Let's say, hypothetically, we have it.

518
00:39:04,977 --> 00:39:06,577
Even if I hand that money over to you,

519
00:39:06,577 --> 00:39:08,563
you're not keeping that promise anyway.

520
00:39:08,563 --> 00:39:10,278
No, I would...

521
00:39:10,278 --> 00:39:11,518
Sure, all right,

522
00:39:11,518 --> 00:39:13,357
I understand why you'd see it that way.

523
00:39:13,357 --> 00:39:15,067
But given the circumstances right now,

524
00:39:15,067 --> 00:39:17,117
we have to have faith in each other, right?

525
00:39:17,117 --> 00:39:19,234
Are you going to kill me?

526
00:39:19,234 --> 00:39:20,526
That's not who you are.

527
00:39:20,526 --> 00:39:23,169
I know you're not that kind of person.
That's why I'm saying all this.

528
00:39:23,169 --> 00:39:25,126
Just a moment.

529
00:39:27,037 --> 00:39:28,998
Wait.

530
00:39:28,998 --> 00:39:32,626
<i>- Hello?</i>
- I'm on my way to the building right now.

531
00:39:32,626 --> 00:39:35,796
Yi Gyeong's bringing her mother along.
I think she's looking to close a deal.

532
00:39:35,796 --> 00:39:38,257
- Right now?
<i>- She's in a real hurry about this.</i>

533
00:39:38,257 --> 00:39:40,384
<i>Turns out you were spot
on about the redevelopment.</i>

534
00:39:40,384 --> 00:39:42,595
See, how many times did I say it?

535
00:39:42,595 --> 00:39:45,347
How often did I say we should never sell?

536
00:39:45,347 --> 00:39:46,849
Understood, I'll be there right away.

537
00:39:46,849 --> 00:39:48,476
I'll be back in a minute.

538
00:39:48,476 --> 00:39:50,352
You said we'd talk about it, but now...

539
00:39:50,352 --> 00:39:52,195
Think about your daughter.

540
00:39:53,522 --> 00:39:56,358
Think about Da Rae's future.

541
00:39:56,358 --> 00:39:58,243
Are you going to become a murderer?

542
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:00,738
You have to think about your daughter.

543
00:40:00,738 --> 00:40:04,874
What would Da Rae think if she saw this?

544
00:40:06,535 --> 00:40:07,787
We need to talk this out...

545
00:40:07,787 --> 00:40:10,171
Da Rae!

546
00:40:12,769 --> 00:40:14,926
[Building Sale Agreement]

547
00:40:16,025 --> 00:40:17,379
I won't waste your time.

548
00:40:17,379 --> 00:40:20,508
I put up 30 percent over market price.

549
00:40:20,508 --> 00:40:22,343
Why?

550
00:40:22,343 --> 00:40:23,469
What do you mean, why?

551
00:40:23,469 --> 00:40:26,764
Why did you go higher than market price?

552
00:40:26,764 --> 00:40:29,608
So you're aware of it.

553
00:40:31,227 --> 00:40:35,189
Yeah, a lot of folks have
had their eye on this building.

554
00:40:35,189 --> 00:40:37,483
This is way out of your league.

555
00:40:37,483 --> 00:40:38,943
Walk away from it.

556
00:40:38,943 --> 00:40:41,153
I'll see that you're well compensated.

557
00:40:41,153 --> 00:40:43,239
Mom, stop.

558
00:40:43,239 --> 00:40:46,992
I've always been grateful for you
caring for my daughter and son-in-law.

559
00:40:46,992 --> 00:40:49,537
I'll keep watching your back.

560
00:40:49,537 --> 00:40:51,671
So hand over the building.

561
00:40:54,250 --> 00:40:56,426
[Building Sale Agreement]

562
00:40:57,087 --> 00:40:59,888
[Vendor, Ki Su Jong, Purchaser, Jeon Yi Gyeong]

563
00:41:02,383 --> 00:41:05,513
We don't have all day, sign and be done.

564
00:41:07,304 --> 00:41:08,472
By the way...

565
00:41:08,472 --> 00:41:10,609
- About Hwal Seong.
- What?

566
00:41:10,609 --> 00:41:12,476
Did you know that Hwal Seong

567
00:41:12,476 --> 00:41:15,028
had his eye on this building?

568
00:41:20,025 --> 00:41:22,150
I...

569
00:41:22,150 --> 00:41:24,613
I want to keep this building a while longer.

570
00:41:24,613 --> 00:41:28,500
There's got to be a reason everyone's after it.

571
00:41:29,493 --> 00:41:33,122
You dismiss my kindness and...

572
00:41:33,122 --> 00:41:36,375
you have no idea how things work.

573
00:41:36,375 --> 00:41:38,002
I already explained to you,

574
00:41:38,002 --> 00:41:41,046
you don't have the capacity to manage this.

575
00:41:41,046 --> 00:41:42,214
Mom.

576
00:41:42,214 --> 00:41:45,175
Yes, I hear everything you're saying.

577
00:41:45,175 --> 00:41:48,637
I have to talk this through with my wife first.

578
00:41:48,637 --> 00:41:50,890
But coming at me this suddenly,

579
00:41:50,890 --> 00:41:52,224
I'm a little thrown off today.

580
00:41:52,224 --> 00:41:53,559
Who's forcing your hand?

581
00:41:53,559 --> 00:41:56,395
I gave you 30 percent over market.

582
00:41:56,395 --> 00:41:59,197
I never asked for that.

583
00:42:00,357 --> 00:42:01,900
You're going to regret this.

584
00:42:01,900 --> 00:42:04,364
It's beyond what you can manage.

585
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:09,585
I'll take care of it well enough myself.

586
00:42:10,492 --> 00:42:11,660
Well...

587
00:42:11,660 --> 00:42:14,580
Let's talk about this another time.

588
00:42:14,580 --> 00:42:16,498
We could use some time to consider too...

589
00:42:16,498 --> 00:42:19,884
Yeah, Mom, this was way too fast today.

590
00:42:22,257 --> 00:42:24,976
Fools who don't know where you stand.

591
00:42:27,801 --> 00:42:29,595
I'm sorry, I'll talk to my mom.

592
00:42:29,595 --> 00:42:31,599
- No, don't worry.
- Don't worry.

593
00:42:35,392 --> 00:42:36,518
Mom!

594
00:42:36,518 --> 00:42:38,319
Mom!

595
00:42:39,355 --> 00:42:41,698
Mom!

596
00:42:44,026 --> 00:42:46,494
Yeah, I have to mull it over.

597
00:42:49,818 --> 00:42:51,700
Mom, please!

598
00:42:51,700 --> 00:42:56,337
Put yourself in other people's shoes too.
Is all this really necessary?

599
00:42:57,081 --> 00:42:58,457
You brainless idiot.

600
00:42:58,457 --> 00:43:01,001
That's exactly why everyone walks over you.

601
00:43:01,001 --> 00:43:04,171
- What?
- You paid off your husband's debt?

602
00:43:04,171 --> 00:43:06,465
How did you find out about that?

603
00:43:06,465 --> 00:43:08,767
You stupid girl.

604
00:43:09,735 --> 00:43:11,553
You knew about it and still didn't help?

605
00:43:11,553 --> 00:43:14,022
Why would I step in for that?

606
00:43:15,599 --> 00:43:17,426
But I...

607
00:43:19,651 --> 00:43:21,446
Yes.

608
00:43:22,356 --> 00:43:25,192
Would it be possible to meet tonight?

609
00:43:25,192 --> 00:43:28,286
There's something I need to ask of you.

610
00:43:30,698 --> 00:43:32,241
Yes.

611
00:43:32,241 --> 00:43:34,000
Yes.

612
00:43:45,546 --> 00:43:46,880
What?

613
00:43:46,880 --> 00:43:49,682
You destroyed my life.

614
00:43:51,010 --> 00:43:53,137
One day

615
00:43:53,137 --> 00:43:56,306
you'll see that I was right.

616
00:43:56,306 --> 00:43:57,391
No.

617
00:43:57,391 --> 00:44:00,527
I'll never turn into a person like you.

618
00:44:06,525 --> 00:44:08,986
Is this really going to work?

619
00:44:08,986 --> 00:44:11,071
Do we have any other option?

620
00:44:11,071 --> 00:44:12,531
That's not what I mean, but...

621
00:44:12,531 --> 00:44:14,832
How about cutting the amount down a little?

622
00:44:16,618 --> 00:44:17,870
No.

623
00:44:17,870 --> 00:44:19,747
Let's just give the original amount.

624
00:44:19,747 --> 00:44:22,257
Yeah, let's do that.

625
00:44:25,377 --> 00:44:28,881
<i>I, Oh Dong Gi, took part as an accomplice
in the abduction of Jeon Yi Gyeong</i>

626
00:44:28,881 --> 00:44:33,719
together with the couple Kim Seon
and Ki Su Jong,

627
00:44:33,719 --> 00:44:36,638
and accepted financial payment in return.

628
00:44:36,638 --> 00:44:39,349
I hereby swear that I will not reveal

629
00:44:39,349 --> 00:44:42,443
this information to any third party
under any circumstances,

630
00:44:43,687 --> 00:44:49,068
and I pledge my life to this vow of silence.

631
00:44:49,068 --> 00:44:50,861
Yes.

632
00:44:50,861 --> 00:44:52,954
Well done.

633
00:44:53,655 --> 00:44:56,450
If you violate this promise, we all fall.

634
00:44:56,450 --> 00:44:58,619
I'll honor it without fail.

635
00:44:58,619 --> 00:45:01,830
One stabbing, two days in captivity,
and a billion won?

636
00:45:01,830 --> 00:45:03,715
Easiest money ever.

637
00:45:15,219 --> 00:45:18,138
- Oh, well...
- Yes, Yi Gyeong.

638
00:45:18,138 --> 00:45:20,023
Oh, what is it?

639
00:45:21,475 --> 00:45:22,684
I'm back.

640
00:45:22,684 --> 00:45:24,978
There's something I need to say to you.

641
00:45:24,978 --> 00:45:28,114
You're down in the basement, correct?

642
00:45:37,533 --> 00:45:38,909
She came to see us.

643
00:45:38,909 --> 00:45:42,704
Stay upstairs for a bit, I'll be right up.

644
00:45:42,704 --> 00:45:43,831
- I'm going.
- Okay.

645
00:45:43,831 --> 00:45:45,965
- Finish up here and follow.
- Yeah.

646
00:45:47,403 --> 00:45:51,332
- Somebody help!
- Come on!

647
00:45:52,131 --> 00:45:54,758
What's gotten into you today?

648
00:45:54,758 --> 00:45:57,226
You really want to die? Huh?

649
00:46:16,280 --> 00:46:19,082
I've got a bloody nose now.

650
00:46:20,576 --> 00:46:22,119
Hey, Yi Gyeong.

651
00:46:22,119 --> 00:46:23,912
Did you catch some kind of noise just now?

652
00:46:23,912 --> 00:46:25,150
What kind of noise?

653
00:46:25,150 --> 00:46:27,666
I thought I heard someone yelling.

654
00:46:27,666 --> 00:46:31,003
The building's pretty dated, so sometimes
noise drifts up from the first floor.

655
00:46:31,003 --> 00:46:32,838
So what brings you here?

656
00:46:32,838 --> 00:46:34,131
Well...

657
00:46:34,131 --> 00:46:37,926
Could we speak somewhere private?

658
00:46:37,926 --> 00:46:39,177
Sure.

659
00:46:39,177 --> 00:46:41,145
How about the rooftop?

660
00:46:42,900 --> 00:46:46,359
I'm sorry, please undo these.

661
00:46:47,526 --> 00:46:49,062
Why won't this open?

662
00:46:49,062 --> 00:46:50,905
What? It won't open?

663
00:46:51,568 --> 00:46:53,783
You're dead.

664
00:46:54,900 --> 00:46:56,153
Who's dead?

665
00:46:56,153 --> 00:46:57,379
Hey.

666
00:46:57,379 --> 00:46:59,026
Mind your language.

667
00:46:59,026 --> 00:47:01,080
I have the handcuff key right here, okay?

668
00:47:01,080 --> 00:47:02,442
This one.

669
00:47:02,442 --> 00:47:03,942
What?

670
00:47:03,942 --> 00:47:05,498
Hold on.

671
00:47:05,498 --> 00:47:07,818
- Where did it go?
- You don't have it?

672
00:47:07,818 --> 00:47:09,570
You really don't have it.

673
00:47:14,257 --> 00:47:16,317
Before anything else...

674
00:47:16,317 --> 00:47:19,651
I need to say sorry about my mom.

675
00:47:19,651 --> 00:47:21,818
It's not your fault.

676
00:47:21,818 --> 00:47:22,888
No, still,

677
00:47:22,888 --> 00:47:26,019
I set up the meeting,

678
00:47:26,019 --> 00:47:29,062
so I'm really sorry and embarrassed.

679
00:47:30,774 --> 00:47:33,196
That's just how family is.

680
00:47:33,968 --> 00:47:36,150
Even when it's humiliating and maddening,

681
00:47:36,150 --> 00:47:38,453
you bear it and move on.

682
00:47:41,159 --> 00:47:44,748
I can't figure out how my life got like this.

683
00:47:44,748 --> 00:47:47,776
Who out there is living better than you?

684
00:47:47,776 --> 00:47:50,423
Hwal Seong's been seeing someone else.

685
00:47:51,042 --> 00:47:53,362
A married woman with a kid, apparently.

686
00:47:53,362 --> 00:47:55,344
And he's been...

687
00:47:58,218 --> 00:48:00,892
talking trash about me with her.

688
00:48:01,554 --> 00:48:04,342
He called me hollow inside,

689
00:48:04,342 --> 00:48:06,981
no appeal, no sense.

690
00:48:09,109 --> 00:48:12,402
He only married me
for my family's wealth, right?

691
00:48:12,402 --> 00:48:15,023
I was young, loaded, and naive,

692
00:48:15,023 --> 00:48:17,482
so he figured he struck gold.

693
00:48:17,482 --> 00:48:20,286
That's not true.

694
00:48:21,201 --> 00:48:24,373
You're such a wonderful person.

695
00:48:26,008 --> 00:48:27,960
Yi Gyeong.

696
00:48:34,963 --> 00:48:37,359
How about a beer?

697
00:48:37,359 --> 00:48:38,930
Yeah.

698
00:48:47,618 --> 00:48:49,737
Drop that thing.

699
00:49:01,003 --> 00:49:03,140
Drop that thing.

700
00:49:03,803 --> 00:49:05,776
Let go, put it down.

701
00:49:05,776 --> 00:49:08,942
- Let go of this.
- A man like Su Jong seems like the real deal.

702
00:49:08,942 --> 00:49:11,859
Huh? In what way?

703
00:49:11,859 --> 00:49:14,465
He's an honest and sincere person.

704
00:49:18,651 --> 00:49:20,359
I wonder who she is.

705
00:49:20,359 --> 00:49:23,052
The woman he's been seeing.

706
00:49:23,052 --> 00:49:25,969
I figured it wouldn't bother me,

707
00:49:25,969 --> 00:49:28,311
but now that I'm the one going through it,

708
00:49:28,311 --> 00:49:30,942
I'm desperate to find out who she is.

709
00:49:30,942 --> 00:49:33,415
What sort of woman would drive him

710
00:49:33,415 --> 00:49:37,109
to have an affair with a married mother?

711
00:49:37,109 --> 00:49:39,448
It's eating me alive.

712
00:49:40,582 --> 00:49:42,694
Is she beautiful?

713
00:49:42,694 --> 00:49:45,371
Attractive? Intelligent?

714
00:49:46,117 --> 00:49:48,424
It's not about that.

715
00:49:49,370 --> 00:49:50,959
What?

716
00:49:52,025 --> 00:49:54,297
It's just...

717
00:49:55,310 --> 00:49:59,051
People don't value what's already theirs.

718
00:49:59,651 --> 00:50:01,952
When they grow dissatisfied with their reality,

719
00:50:01,952 --> 00:50:04,442
they start craving
what belongs to someone else.

720
00:50:04,442 --> 00:50:06,750
That's simply how people are.

721
00:50:06,750 --> 00:50:08,513
Whether someone's superior or inferior,

722
00:50:08,513 --> 00:50:11,981
none of that truly matters.

723
00:50:12,723 --> 00:50:13,978
It's not your problem.

724
00:50:13,978 --> 00:50:16,068
It's his problem.

725
00:50:19,959 --> 00:50:22,020
Seon.

726
00:50:22,020 --> 00:50:25,647
What should I read to speak the way you do?

727
00:50:25,647 --> 00:50:27,887
Please tell me.

728
00:50:27,887 --> 00:50:30,042
Oh, stop, there's nothing cool about it.

729
00:50:30,042 --> 00:50:31,025
- Hey.
- I dropped it.

730
00:50:31,025 --> 00:50:32,888
- Okay.
- I told you I dropped it.

731
00:50:32,888 --> 00:50:34,738
Catch your breath then, let's just relax.

732
00:50:34,738 --> 00:50:36,964
Let's cool down.

733
00:50:45,484 --> 00:50:47,692
Remember that?

734
00:50:47,692 --> 00:50:49,518
Remember what?

735
00:50:50,442 --> 00:50:52,900
The good landlord thing.

736
00:50:52,900 --> 00:50:54,224
During COVID?

737
00:50:54,224 --> 00:50:57,526
Yeah, when my shop had just opened.

738
00:50:58,526 --> 00:50:59,855
Those were good times.

739
00:50:59,855 --> 00:51:01,484
[Good Landlord Campaign! 30% rent cut!]

740
00:51:01,484 --> 00:51:04,575
The latte was at its finest back then.

741
00:51:06,942 --> 00:51:08,908
You only did that

742
00:51:08,908 --> 00:51:10,899
to get the tax benefit, right?

743
00:51:10,899 --> 00:51:12,000
Don't be ridiculous.

744
00:51:12,000 --> 00:51:14,335
That's just how the law works.

745
00:51:15,192 --> 00:51:16,963
What are you doing?

746
00:51:19,609 --> 00:51:21,628
Talking about the law, my ass.

747
00:51:21,628 --> 00:51:23,601
What a masterclass in being cheap.

748
00:51:23,601 --> 00:51:24,818
I've got your number now, huh?

749
00:51:24,818 --> 00:51:27,749
Hey. Knock it off and release me already.

750
00:51:27,749 --> 00:51:30,651
Thank you so much for today's talk.

751
00:51:30,651 --> 00:51:31,949
Oh, it was nothing.

752
00:51:31,949 --> 00:51:34,139
Whenever you need me, just say the word.

753
00:51:34,139 --> 00:51:36,928
Let's really see each other more often.

754
00:51:36,928 --> 00:51:38,668
Sounds good.

755
00:51:42,400 --> 00:51:44,031
Die.

756
00:51:44,692 --> 00:51:45,776
Die.

757
00:51:45,776 --> 00:51:47,618
Die, you bastard.

758
00:52:06,983 --> 00:52:09,557
What? He didn't come out?

759
00:52:13,859 --> 00:52:15,730
What's wrong with this thing?

760
00:52:20,484 --> 00:52:22,479
What on earth did I do so wrong?

761
00:52:22,479 --> 00:52:23,983
Su Jong!

762
00:52:23,983 --> 00:52:26,319
The money would've settled it.

763
00:52:26,319 --> 00:52:28,150
I literally wet myself because of you.

764
00:52:28,150 --> 00:52:31,162
- Die.
- Let's stop this.

765
00:52:31,983 --> 00:52:33,526
Honey.

766
00:52:33,526 --> 00:52:35,499
Let's get out of here.

767
00:53:14,182 --> 00:53:18,641
I want us to repeat what we did last time.

768
00:53:18,641 --> 00:53:20,651
Go to Se Yoon Building

769
00:53:20,651 --> 00:53:22,642
and create a building defect?

770
00:53:22,642 --> 00:53:25,282
There's nothing complicated about it.

771
00:53:25,282 --> 00:53:28,715
Just go blow out a couple of pipes and leave.

772
00:53:28,715 --> 00:53:30,615
Don't you think

773
00:53:30,615 --> 00:53:33,475
we're too old for that kind of thing?

774
00:53:33,475 --> 00:53:36,310
We're better than the young ones.

775
00:53:48,692 --> 00:53:50,692
Do we really have to go that far?

776
00:53:50,692 --> 00:53:54,585
If you had any idea what humiliation
I went through today,

777
00:53:54,585 --> 00:53:57,289
you'd take that back.

778
00:54:03,663 --> 00:54:06,018
[If you cling to your life, you will lose it]

779
00:54:06,018 --> 00:54:09,135
[But if you give up your life for me,
you will find it]

780
00:54:41,830 --> 00:54:44,942
I can lend you the equipment.

781
00:54:44,942 --> 00:54:47,310
But that's as far as I go.

782
00:54:47,310 --> 00:54:50,010
You won't get your hands dirty?

783
00:54:50,010 --> 00:54:53,971
I'm acquainted with that building owner too.

784
00:54:54,843 --> 00:54:57,391
I've got my own set of rules.

785
00:55:01,243 --> 00:55:02,906
Fine.

786
00:55:03,848 --> 00:55:07,313
Doing it myself suits me better anyway.

787
00:55:07,313 --> 00:55:10,552
Every filthy job, tough job, risky job,

788
00:55:10,552 --> 00:55:14,532
I've taken care of it all by myself.
That's how I made it to where I am.

789
00:55:14,532 --> 00:55:16,255
Why?

790
00:55:17,109 --> 00:55:20,873
Because people can never be trusted.

791
00:55:27,609 --> 00:55:29,757
You'll regret it.

792
00:55:30,834 --> 00:55:34,094
I've been regretting things for a long time.

793
00:55:45,484 --> 00:55:47,274
It's going to sting.

794
00:55:51,676 --> 00:55:53,676
Dong Gi will be okay, right?

795
00:55:53,676 --> 00:55:56,608
Yeah. He's a bit roughed up, though.

796
00:55:57,322 --> 00:55:59,446
It's done.

797
00:55:59,446 --> 00:56:01,818
What do we do now?

798
00:56:01,818 --> 00:56:03,495
I don't know either.

799
00:56:03,495 --> 00:56:05,542
All we can do is wait and see.

800
00:56:07,256 --> 00:56:09,516
That son of a bitch Hwal Seong,

801
00:56:09,516 --> 00:56:11,692
I should've refused
when he brought up the kidnapping.

802
00:56:11,692 --> 00:56:14,051
I must've lost my mind back then,

803
00:56:14,669 --> 00:56:17,356
convinced I needed to save the building.

804
00:56:17,356 --> 00:56:19,263
No.

805
00:56:19,263 --> 00:56:22,456
You gave it everything you had.

806
00:56:22,456 --> 00:56:24,728
It was all for our sake.

807
00:56:26,651 --> 00:56:29,858
If I end up in prison, will you bring me meals?

808
00:56:33,234 --> 00:56:35,156
You think it'd just be you?

809
00:56:35,156 --> 00:56:36,277
I'll be right there with you.

810
00:56:36,277 --> 00:56:37,904
No, that's not an option.

811
00:56:37,904 --> 00:56:39,360
You need to look after Da Rae.

812
00:56:39,360 --> 00:56:41,234
She's got her operation, university,

813
00:56:41,234 --> 00:56:43,076
and eventually a wedding ahead of her.

814
00:56:43,076 --> 00:56:45,609
As long as we hold onto that money,

815
00:56:45,609 --> 00:56:47,584
